## Memory Source File Conventions

Files in `data/memories/`:
- `identity.md` — who the agent is, core personality, owner
- `user_preferences.md` — operator preferences, communication style
- `long_term.md` — curated long-term facts, important decisions, key relationships
- `capabilities.md` — what skills are available and when to use each
- `instructions.md` — behavioral rules, things to always or never do

Adding a new memory file:
1. Create the `.md` file with `# category` headings and `- key: value` entries
2. Assign priorities with `<!-- priority:1 -->` comments (default: 2)
3. Sentinel will detect the new file and trigger recompilation automatically
4. Check token count: `make health | jq .memory`
